
The following instructions may help you veriifying your QSTK installation on Fedora:


1 - Install required packages:

  $ sudo yum install unzip blas blas-devel lapack lapack-devel numpy scipy gcc-c++ python-matplotlib ipython python-pandas sympy pytz python-dateutil python-qt4 python-nose python python-cvxopt python-devel python-setuptools python-pip


2 - Install QSTK and other python extensions (--user installs it in your user directory):

  $ sudo pip-python install scikit-learn scikits.statsmodels qstk


3 - Verify installation:

  $ wget https://spark-public.s3.amazonaws.com/compinvesting1/QSTK-Setups/Examples.zip
  $ unzip Examples.zip
  $ cd Examples
  $ python Validation.py


Hope this helps!


References:

  https://piazza.com/class/hinh62c9pjm17g?cid=78
  https://gist.github.com/pmembrey/5088667
  http://wiki.quantsoftware.org/index.php?title=QSToolKit_Installation_Guide_Windows

